Enum StatementModifier.StatementModifierType

    StatementModifier

    public static enum StatementModifier.StatementModifierType
extends java.lang.Enum<StatementModifier.StatementModifierType>
    Defines the type of the statement modifier.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      Automatic
      Indicates if the statement was automatically generatied by a compiler or other system.
      Choose
      Has a value that indicates how many rows to randomly select out of the statement's SELECT statement.
      ChooseMinimum
      Has an additional value that indicates the minimum number of results required in the Choose
      Delete
      The statement (a clause) is a delete statement, as opposed to the default, append statement.
      End
      A statement that is to appear at the end of the recursive rule evaluation
      None 
      Periodic
      The statement (a clause) is periodic and has an Integer data object specifying the expected periodicity in msec
      PreviousTable
      Used on table declarations and identifies the table as a primary table that have its values copied to the previous table named by the value of this modifier.
      PrimaryTable
      Used on table declarations and identifies the table as a previous table that will hold the values of the primary table named by the value of this modifier.
